panels.description:
Warning (yellow) if one or more of the following conditions are true:

1) Idle CPU is less than 20%.
2) Load is higher than 5
3) Free memory is less than 1000 MiB;
4) Free space of "/" is less than 10 GiB;

Critial (red) if one or more of the following conditions are true:

1) Idle CPU is less than 5%.
2) Load is higher than 10
3) Free space of "/" is less than 1 GiB;
4) Free memory is less than 100 MiB;

The system load is defined as the number of runnable tasks in the run-queue and is provided by many operating systems as a one minute average.
